Heat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Place 1 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave in ~{10-15%second} intervals until melted. Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; season with salt, pepper, and half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a second medium #bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Meanwhile, heat another large drizzle of olive oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and remaining Tuscan Heat Spice; cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Reduce heat to medium low.

Add @marinara cup{14%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and chicken to pan. Stir in drained penne, 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water (½ cup for 4 servings), and 2 TBSP butter (3 TBSP for 4). Season with salt (start with ½ tsp, taste, and add more from there) and pepper. If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture to a #baking dish{}.

Sprinkle pasta mixture with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup} and panko. Broil or bake until cheese is melted and bubbly and panko is golden, ~{2-4%minutes}. Serve straight from the pan.

> Watch carefully for any burning when broiling.